==========================================================================================
Section 1 : Information regarding the tbb-mat-vect-malloc directory structure.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
include/       --> consists of header files
src/           --> contains README file and main file
                   README - Gives quick information regarding Package and how to execute
                   the code.
lib/           --> contains file having function definitions.

=============================================================================================
Section 2 : Steps for using  tbb-mat-vect-malloc
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy the "tbb-mat-vect-malloc.tar". Untar the file using
         $tar -xvf  tbb-mat-vect-malloc


in your home directory. This will create folder "tbb-mat-vect-malloc"

The following directory structure of  tbb-mat-vect-malloc  will be created in the
main directory i.e "tbb-mat-vect-malloc".

          /include        /src          /lib


==============================================================================================
Section 3 : Pre-Requisites.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TBB2.0 should be installed and configured with Linux /Unix OS.

===============================================================================================
Section 4 : Steps for compiling  tbb-mat-vect-malloc
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Go in the respective directory
and give
         make


===============================================================================================
Section 5 : Steps for executing  tbb-mat-vect-malloc
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


	./name_of_executable  size  Number-of-threads



